(146, 'CYBER CRIME AND HUMAN RIGHTS by David Penfold.pdf', 'Cyber Crime And Human Rights', NULL, 'David Penfold', 'It has been reported in the news that Chinese hackers are defacing US government sites and, in turn, US hackers are defacing Chinese government sites. At the same time, in the UK, a National Hi-Tech Crime Unit (NHTCU) has been set up to investigate paedophilia, fraud, extortion, hacking and copyright abuse. My initial reaction is to deplore the first of these and praise the second. However, as so often, the situation is not that simple.', 'MicrosoftÂ® Word 2010', 'MicrosoftÂ® Word 2010', 157274, '10/24/2025, 5:58:29 PM', 'D:20150806132701+03\'00\'', 'D:20150806132701+03\'00\'', 'en-US', NULL, 1.5, b'0', b'0', b'0', b'0', b'0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Computer Crime Research Center', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'null', b'0', '1761317909524', 'null', '2002', 'Cybersecurity and human rights', 'application/pdf', '2025-10-25 15:04:11', '2025-10-30 19:57:06'),
(147, 'Cyber Security, Cyber Surveillance and Online Human Rights.pdf', 'Cyber Security, Cyber Surveillance And Online Human Rights', NULL, 'Anja Kovacs; Dixie Hawtin', 'If activists are to win the fight to keep the Internet free and open, it is becoming increasingly clear that they must familiarise themselves intimately with the areas of cyber security and cyber surveillance. International state-sponsored cyber espionage has given birth to the twin narratives of cyber war and a cyber arms race; narratives which are being used in some parts of the world to encourage citizens to trade in civil liberties for a greater sense of security. In the US, for instance, cyber espionage by Chinese hackers is a key argument used to support the controversial Cyber Intelligence Sharing and Protection Act (CISPA) which would enable the authorities to access vast amounts of user data without a warrant.', 'MicrosoftÂ® Word 2010', 'MicrosoftÂ® Word 2010', 171864, '10/24/2025, 5:58:29 PM', 'D:20130516152645+02\'00\'', 'D:20170403234103+03\'00\'', 'sv-SE', NULL, 1.5, b'0', b'0', b'1', b'0', b'0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Anja Kovacs; Dixie Hawtin', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'null', b'0', '1761317909545', NULL, '2013', 'Cybersecurity and human rights', 'application/pdf', '2025-10-25 15:04:11', '2025-10-30 19:59:17'),
(148, 'Cybersecurity and Human Rights.pdf', 'Cyber Security And Human Rights', NULL, 'Natalie Green; Carolina Rossini', 'This will serve as an introduction to cyber security with a particular focus on the policy aspect of cyber security, including how cyber security is addressed in international relations and the impact cyber security has on human rights. By the end of the module, you should be able to answer the following questions: ● What role do “definitions” play in cyber security debates, discussions, and policy decisions? ● What are the main human rights concerns when dealing with cyber security? ● Are there international laws and standards that apply to cyber security? Do they address human rights concerns? ● How is cyber security addressed regionally and internationally?', 'MicrosoftÂ® Office Word 2007', 'MicrosoftÂ® Office Word 2007', 227211, '10/24/2025, 5:58:29 PM', 'D:20150312104851Z', 'D:20170403234124+03\'00\'', 'en-GB', NULL, 1.5, b'0', b'0', b'1', b'0', b'0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Public Knowledge', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'null', b'0', '1761317909603', NULL, '2014', 'Cybersecurity and human rights', 'application/pdf', '2025-10-25 15:04:11', '2025-10-30 20:06:08'),
(149, 'Futuribles-CIGREF-Entreprises-cybersecurite.pdf', 'Entreprises Et Cybersécurité à L’ Horizon 2020', NULL, 'Cécile Wendling Puis; François De Jouvenel; Nicolas Mazzucchi', 'Les risques cyber évoluent vite, obligeant les entreprises et les administrations publiques à réagir sur des temps très courts. Néanmoins, une approche uniquement réactive des ques tions de cybersécurité est préjudiciable à la mise en œuvre de stratégies efficientes sur cette question. L’étude réalisée par Futuribles International a pour ambition de replacer les enjeux de cybersécurité dans une perspective systémique et stratégique de moyen terme qui soit utile à la mise en place de stratégies de réduction des risques à différentes échelles (États, entre prises, individus). Le but de cette étude est donc de proposer aux organismes qui y ont par ticipé une vision claire et documentée des évolutions possibles de leur environnement d’ici 2020 qui leur soit utile pour concevoir leurs stratégies de cybersécurité.', 'MicrosoftÂ® Word 2010', 'MicrosoftÂ® Word 2010', 547406, '10/24/2025, 5:58:29 PM', 'D:20150213082148+01\'00\'', 'D:20170404141018+03\'00\'', 'fr-FR', NULL, 1.6, b'0', b'0', b'1', b'0', b'0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Futuribles International', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'null', b'0', '1761317909667', NULL, '2015', 'Cybersecurity and human rights', 'application/pdf', '2025-10-25 15:04:11', '2025-10-30 20:10:14'),
